gilante]]. Using [[Walter Steele (Arrowverse)|Walter Steele]]'s help, Oliver saves his company and forces Rochev to accept a partnership. Thea reconciles with Moira. Oliver decides to honor Tommy's memory by becoming a hero in Starling City, and finding a new name for his alter-ego. In a flashback, Oliver, [[Shado (Arrowverse)|Shado]], and [[Slade Wilson (Arrowverse)|Slade Wilson]] encounter new armed men after months of believing to be alone. The newcomers are revealed to be searching some specific graves.\n| LineColor       = 424C40\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Arrow (season 2)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 25\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| Title           = Identity\n| DirectedBy      = [[Nick Copus]]\n| WrittenBy       = [[Ben Sokolowski]] & [[Beth Schwartz]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|10|16}}\n| ProdCode        = 2J7452\n| Viewers         = 3.06<ref name=\"2.02\">{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/17/wednesday-final-ratings-modern-family-law-nashville-ironside-adjusted-down/209795 |title=Wednesday Final Ratings: ''Modern Family'', ''Law & Order: SVU'', ''Survivor'', ''Toy Story of TERROR!'' & ''Back in the Game'' Adjusted Up; ''Nashville'' & ''Ironside'' Adjusted Down |last=Bibel |first=Sara |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=October 17, 2013 |accessdate=October 17, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020052002/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/17/wednesday-final-ratings-modern-family-law-nashville-ironside-adjusted-down/209795/ |archive-date=October 20, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Roy fails to stop a truck robbery committed by [[Chien Na Wei (Arrowverse)|Chien Na Wei]]. When Oliver attempts to convince Roy to stop being a vigilante, Oliver learns that the hospital in the Glades is having its medicine stolen. Oliver sets a trap for Chien, who escapes after having [[Ben Turner (Arrowverse)|clawed henchman]] fight him; the police arrive and the two escape. Diggle is revealed to have ended his relationship with [[Carly Diggle|Carly]]. Oliver decides to work with [[Sebastian Blood (Arrowverse)|Sebastian Blood]], an alderman for the Glades, to bring awareness and help for the people in need, but is forced to abandon his appearance at the charity event to instead stop Chien, who gets arrested. Blood lambastes him in the press for that. The vigilante convinces Roy to stop fighting in his name, but instead provide him intel in the Glades. Afterward, Laurel, blaming the vigilante for Tommy's death, sets a trap for him, who gets seemingly surrounded by the police. In a flashback, Slade advises Oliver not to let his relationship with Shado get too serious. The trio discovers a cave containing the remains of several cranially disfigured [[World War II]] [[Japanese Imperial Army|Japanese soldiers]].\n| LineColor       = 424C40\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Arrow (season 2)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 26\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = Broken Dolls\n| DirectedBy      = [[Glen Winter]]\n| WrittenBy       = Marc Guggenheim & [[Keto Shimizu]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|10|23}}\n| ProdCode        = 2J7453\n| Viewers         = 2.89<ref name=\"2.03\">{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/24/wednesday-final-ratings-survivor-the-middle-modern-family-super-fun-night-adjusted-down-final-world-series-numbers/211151 |title=Wednesday Final Ratings: ''Survivor'', ''The Middle'', ''Modern Family'' & ''The Tomorrow People'' Adjusted Up; ''Super Fun Night'' Adjusted Down + Final World Series Numbers |last=Kondolojy |first=Amanda |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=October 24, 2013 |accessdate=October 24, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140702230327/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/24/wednesday-final-ratings-survivor-the-middle-modern-family-super-fun-night-adjusted-down-final-world-series-numbers/211151 |archive-date=July 2, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Oliver assigns Roy to track a woman who inadvertently tries to be a vigilante, which he manages through her connection to a woman named [[Cindy Simone|Cindy]]. Quentin discovers that the serial killer [[Barton Mathis (Arrowverse)|Barton Mathis]], whom he arrested years earlier, escaped from prison during the earthquake and is on the killing spree again. Believing the vigilante's claim to have changed, Quentin enlists his help. The team discovers the link between all of the victims. Oliver learns that Mathis has abducted Quentin and Laurel and plans to kill the latter. Oliver saves them before the female vigilante shows up and kills Mathis. Oliver believes that she has a personal connection with him. Laurel states that she must blame herself instead of the vigilante for Tommy's death. The District Attorney announces his intention to seek the death penalty for Moira. She tells her lawyer not to fight it, since she had connections with [[Malcolm Merlyn (Arrowverse)|Malcolm Merlyn]] that she does not want revealed to her children. The female vigilante kills an operative of [[Ra's al Ghul (Arrowverse)|Ra's al Ghul]], her former master. In flashbacks to the island, a ship starts bombarding Oliver and Slade. Oliver finds himself imprisoned with other inmates in a ship called the \"Amazo\".\n| LineColor       = 424C40\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Arrow (season 2)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 27\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Crucible\n| DirectedBy      = [[Eagle Egilsson]]\n| WrittenBy       = Andrew Kreisberg & [[Wendy Mericle]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2013|10|30}}\n| ProdCode        = 2J7454\n| Viewers         = 2.37<ref name=\"2.04\">{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/10/31/wednesday-final-ratings-arrow-super-fun-night-csi-adjusted-down-final-world-series-numbers/212682 |title=Wednesday Final Ratings: ''Arrow'' & ''The Middle'' Adjusted Up; ''Super Fun Night'' & ''CSI'' Adjusted Down & Final World Series Numbers |last=Bibel |first=Sara |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=October 31, 2013 |accessdat